cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV. 

The paper proposes a neural model for document ranking, which is a common task in information retrieval (IR). Therefore, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category. The model uses word embeddings, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML), suggesting cs.CL as the second likely sub-category. The model also uses a learning-to-rank layer, which is a common technique in ML, suggesting cs.LG as the third likely sub-category. The model uses kernels, which are commonly used in ML and computer vision (CV), suggesting cs.AI and cs.CV as the fourth and fifth likely sub-categories, respectively.
